          <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrc="dd:2;55:15" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/relatedSubjects.dita">On this element, the <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:11;55:44" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/relatedSubjects.dita">linking</xmlatt> attribute has a default value of
            "normal". Otherwise, the attribute is the same as defined in <xref class="- topic/xref " href="../attributes/commonMapAttributes.dita" keyref="attributes-commonMap" xtrc="xref:7;57:46" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/base/relatedSubjects.dita" type="reference"><?ditaot gentext?>Attributes common to many map elements<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">This attribute group collects several attributes that are used on a variety of map   elements. For a few elements, the group is modified slightly to remove an attribute such as    <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:1;8:12" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/attributes/commonMapAttributes.dita">toc</xmlatt> or <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:2;8:36" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/attributes/commonMapAttributes.dita">format</xmlatt>; in those cases the element definition will   clarify that the element does not use this full set. That is generally done in order to specify a   default for one attribute, such as defaulting <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:3;10:57" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/attributes/commonMapAttributes.dita">format</xmlatt> to "ditamap" on the    <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:1;11:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/langRef/attributes/commonMapAttributes.dita">mapref</xmlelement> element.</desc></xref>.</dd>
